The article discusses a letter from President Barack Obama to Congress regarding the deployment of US military personnel to central Africa to support regional forces in their efforts to apprehend or remove Joseph Kony, the leader of the Lord's Resistance Army (LRA). The deployment includes approximately 150 additional personnel who will operate and maintain US aircraft to provide air mobility support. The total number of US military personnel deployed for this mission is now approximately 280, with the possibility of increasing to around 300. The letter states that US forces will only engage the LRA if necessary in self-defense and highlights that this deployment is in line with the national security and foreign policy interests of the United States. The letter is being sent in accordance with the War Powers Resolution to keep Congress informed.